A civil servant, Aremu Balogun, who allegedly beat up his creditor, on Wednesday appeared in an Ikeja Chief Magistrates’ Court. <img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-1265514" src="https://i2.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/court-symbol.jpg?resize=640%2C360&#038;ssl=1" alt="court, Businessman" width="640" height="360" srcset="https://i2.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/court-symbol.jpg?w=1280&amp;ssl=1 1280w, https://i2.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/court-symbol.jpg?resize=300%2C169&amp;ssl=1 300w, https://i2.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/court-symbol.jpg?resize=768%2C432&amp;ssl=1 768w, https://i2.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/court-symbol.jpg?resize=1024%2C576&amp;ssl=1 1024w, https://i2.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/court-symbol.jpg?resize=58%2C33&amp;ssl=1 58w, https://i2.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/court-symbol.jpg?resize=260%2C146&amp;ssl=1 260w, https://i2.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/court-symbol.jpg?resize=200%2C113&amp;ssl=1 200w, https://i2.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/court-symbol.jpg?resize=560%2C315&amp;ssl=1 560w" sizes="(max-width: 640px) 100vw, 640px" data-recalc-dims="1" /> Balogun, 49, who resides at No. 9, Adealu St., Dopemu, Lagos, is charged with conspiracy, assault and stealing. He pleaded not guilty. The Prosecution Counsel, Insp. Victor Eruada told the court that Balogun committed the offence on Sept. 28, at Adebambo Junction, Off Adealu St., Dopemu, Lagos. Eruada alleged that the defendant beat up the complainant, Mr Emmanuel Ogunji when he asked him to pay the N4,000, for the drinks he bought from him. He also alleged that the defendant stole Ogunji’s wristwatch, necklace, gold ring all valued at  N58,230. The offence, he said, contravened the provisions of sections 411, 173 and 287 of the Criminal Laws of Lagos State, 2015. News Agency of Nigeria (NAN) reports that Section 173 provides a three-year jail term for assault while Section 287 prescribes three years imprisonment for stealing. Chief Magistrate M.I. Dan-Oni admitted the defendant to bail in the sum of N300, 000 with two sureties in like sum. Dan-Oni adjourned the case until Nov. 20 for hearing. Vanguard The police on Monday arraigned two sisters, Rasidat Lasisi and Ramota Shoyoye, in an Ikeja Magistrates’ Court for allegedly attacking their tenant with razor blades during a disagreement. March 25, 2019 In "Crime Alert" A 26-year-old man, Taiwo Fatoki,  on Monday appeared before an Ikeja Magistrates’ Court for allegedly stealing  a a tricycle worth N650,000. October 7, 2019 In "News" A 39-year-old tricycle driver, Agboola Seun, who allegedly assaulted a police officer, was on Wednesday brought before an Ikeja Magistrates’ Court,  Lagos. September 6, 2017 In "News"